abstract: An environmental activist has organized an unlikely group to protest the project: Nebraska ranchers and farmers.
snippet: An environmental activist has organized an unlikely group to protest the project: Nebraska ranchers and farmers.
lead_paragraph: Terry Van Housen had a question. What he wanted to know from the 30 or so other Nebraska farmers and ranchers gathered in February at the York Community Center was this: What do you do with 10,000 dead cows?

abstract: Rich students complete their college degrees; working-class students like Vanessa Brewer usually don’t. Can the University of Texas change her chances of success?
snippet: Rich students complete their college degrees; working-class students like Vanessa Brewer usually don’t. Can the University of Texas change her chances of success?
lead_paragraph: For as long as she could remember, Vanessa Brewer had her mind set on going to college. The image of herself as a college student appealed to her — independent, intelligent, a young woman full of potential — but it was more than that; it was a chance to rewrite the ending to a family story that went off track 18 years earlier, when Vanessa’s mother, then a high-achieving high-school senior in a small town in Arkansas, became pregnant with Vanessa.

abstract: Sylvia Mathews Burwell, the nominee for secretary of health and human services, was called “a force for bringing people together” at her Senate confirmation hearing Wednesday.
snippet: Sylvia Mathews Burwell, the nominee for secretary of health and human services, was called “a force for bringing people together” at her Senate confirmation hearing Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Sylvia Mathews Burwell, President Obama’s nominee for secretary of health and human services, appeared Wednesday to be on a swift path to confirmation after she sailed through another cordial congressional hearing without promising significant changes in federal health policy or regulations.

abstract: Under Mayor Bill de Blasio, the longtime fraternity of city government looks more like a sorority, with women outnumbering men in the administration’s top ranks.
snippet: Under Mayor Bill de Blasio, the longtime fraternity of city government looks more like a sorority, with women outnumbering men in the administration’s top ranks.
lead_paragraph: With Manhattan still cloaked in early-morning darkness, New York City’s new sanitation commissioner stepped into a semicircle of 40 men holding brooms and dustpans as they finished roll call and prepared to clean the streets of the Village.
